Description: Fragment of oval handle of a Rhodian pottery transport amphora from neck join to sharpish turn. Clay fine pink-red; cream slip. Rectangular stamp with Helios head symbol.
Production date: 174 BC (see N. Badoud, Le temps de Rhodes (2015) 142.)
Curator's comments: Name Kleukrates. From same die as Alexandria, Greco-Roman Museum, ABC 0162.18. Trimmed.
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (JB.0903)
